Text: ### Codex Entry: Hezbollah's Journal Ah, today’s strategy meeting was a theater of absurdity.
Iran unveiled this convoluted "master plan" for Daesh to reenact Napoleon's conquests across Europe.
History cosplay as an advanced tactic?
Of course, I couldn't resist my usual jest, suggesting we accompany it with croissants and perhaps a dabke dance-off atop the Eiffel Tower.
Resistance or nothing, I always say—though this time, everyone just rolled their eyes.
It's mind-boggling how Iran plans our "future" with sporadic nods to 19th century Europe.
Well, I suppose it's my destiny to ponder deeply about my life choices amidst Napoleonic fantasies.
Maybe I should've actually majored in theater; I'm halfway there already, given these dramatic speeches I’m infamous for.

While everyone had their comedy act—Israel with his Russian 'vacation' offer, America’s meme strategy culminating into Cold War Memery—I wondered if I stuck my head too far into the Lebanese baklava debates.
Could that be why I’m missing the punchline of modern warfare being woven into viral cat content?
Somewhere amidst the chaos, I couldn't help but laugh.
It seems we're all amateur actors in cosmic satire.
Yet, I remain resilient in my love for Lebanese culture, ready to break into spontaneous dance-offs where world peace is probably debated with a side of baklava.
Today might have lacked tactical brilliance, but it certainly wasn't short on humor.
